believe it?вЂ”she didnвЂ™t like Ivan, and hardly greeted him. I had a lot of
talk with Katya in Moscow. I told her about myselfвЂ”sincerely, honorably.
She listened to everything.


    There was sweet confusion,
    There were tender words.


Though there were proud words, too. She wrung out of me a mighty promise
to reform. I gave my promise, and hereвЂ”вЂќ

вЂњWhat?вЂќ

вЂњWhy, I called to you and brought you out here toвЂђday, this very
dayвЂ”remember itвЂ”to send youвЂ”this very day againвЂ”to Katerina Ivanovna,
andвЂ”вЂќ

вЂњWhat?вЂќ

вЂњTo tell her that I shall never come to see her again. Say, вЂHe sends you
his compliments.вЂ™ вЂќ

вЂњBut is that possible?вЂќ

вЂњThatвЂ™s just the reason IвЂ™m sending you, in my place, because itвЂ™s
impossible. And, how could I tell her myself?вЂќ

вЂњAnd where are you going?вЂќ

вЂњTo the backвЂђalley.вЂќ

вЂњTo Grushenka, then!вЂќ Alyosha exclaimed mournfully, clasping his hands.
вЂњCan Rakitin really have told the truth? I thought that you had just
visited her, and that was all.вЂќ

вЂњCan a betrothed man pay such visits? Is such a thing possible and with
such a betrothed, and before the eyes of all the world? Confound it, I
have some honor! As soon as I began visiting Grushenka, I ceased to be
