it would be enough to put your finger on the ax and it would be the end of
it ... if only there could be an ax there.вЂќ

вЂњAnd can there be an ax there?вЂќ Ivan interrupted, carelessly and
disdainfully. He was exerting himself to the utmost not to believe in the
delusion and not to sink into complete insanity.

вЂњAn ax?вЂќ the guest interrupted in surprise.

вЂњYes, what would become of an ax there?вЂќ Ivan cried suddenly, with a sort
of savage and insistent obstinacy.

вЂњWhat would become of an ax in space? _Quelle idГ©e!_ If it were to fall to
any distance, it would begin, I think, flying round the earth without
knowing why, like a satellite. The astronomers would calculate the rising
and the setting of the ax, _Gatzuk_ would put it in his calendar, thatвЂ™s
