вЂњYou are stupid, awfully stupid,вЂќ said Ivan peevishly. вЂњFib more cleverly
or I wonвЂ™t listen. You want to get the better of me by realism, to
convince me that you exist, but I donвЂ™t want to believe you exist! I wonвЂ™t
believe it!вЂќ

вЂњBut I am not fibbing, itвЂ™s all the truth; the truth is unhappily hardly
ever amusing. I see you persist in expecting something big of me, and
perhaps something fine. ThatвЂ™s a great pity, for I only give what I canвЂ”вЂќ

вЂњDonвЂ™t talk philosophy, you ass!вЂќ

вЂњPhilosophy, indeed, when all my right side is numb and I am moaning and
groaning. IвЂ™ve tried all the medical faculty: they can diagnose
