letter of thanks if itвЂ™s anonymous? I laughed with the men at the
newspaper office; вЂItвЂ™s reactionary to believe in God in our days,вЂ™ I
said, вЂbut I am the devil, so I may be believed in.вЂ™ вЂWe quite understand
that,вЂ™ they said. вЂWho doesnвЂ™t believe in the devil? Yet it wonвЂ™t do, it
might injure our reputation. As a joke, if you like.вЂ™ But I thought as a
joke it wouldnвЂ™t be very witty. So it wasnвЂ™t printed. And do you know, I
have felt sore about it to this day. My best feelings, gratitude, for
instance, are literally denied me simply from my social position.вЂќ

вЂњPhilosophical reflections again?вЂќ Ivan snarled malignantly.

вЂњGod preserve me from it, but one canвЂ™t help complaining sometimes. I am a
slandered man. You upbraid me every moment with being stupid. One can see
you are young. My dear fellow, intelligence isnвЂ™t the only thing! I have
naturally a kind and merry heart. вЂI also write vaudevilles of all sorts.вЂ™
