give away all this superвЂђstellar life, all the ranks and honors, simply to
be transformed into the soul of a merchantвЂ™s wife weighing eighteen stone
and set candles at GodвЂ™s shrine.вЂќ

вЂњThen even you donвЂ™t believe in God?вЂќ said Ivan, with a smile of hatred.

вЂњWhat can I say?вЂ”that is, if you are in earnestвЂ”вЂќ

вЂњIs there a God or not?вЂќ Ivan cried with the same savage intensity.

вЂњAh, then you are in earnest! My dear fellow, upon my word I donвЂ™t know.
There! IвЂ™ve said it now!вЂќ

вЂњYou donвЂ™t know, but you see God? No, you are not some one apart, you are
myself, you are I and nothing more! You are rubbish, you are my fancy!вЂќ

вЂњWell, if you like, I have the same philosophy as you, that would be true.
